execute as @s[scores={rr.trigger.knowledge_id=1}] run tellraw @s {"text":"I have regained my composure. And now, I may tell you how much I despise this place. It reeks beyond comprehension. And every step down each barely-lit corridor gives me the worst chills. May Benevolence herself set ablaze every inch of this tainted world. This sculk infection has bred a monster most hideous through the hundreds of souls lost in this crypt, and I believe the tales told by the survivors are still unable to do it justice. Indeed, the Empire should have remained cautious when dealing with this sculk. Now, it has birthed this Necrosculker, and I fear that it answers to something greater than itself. Just what unrelenting hell has haunted our lands with this beast?","color":"aqua"}
execute as @s[scores={rr.trigger.knowledge_id=2}] run tellraw @s {"text":"Some months have passed since I first saw this monstrosity. I am still deeply disturbed by this place, but I found some way to calm my spirit. However, upon further inspection, I have found new horrors to reawaken my festering worries. There is a hierarchy of these Necrosculkers. I have slain the strongest of the ones I have faced thus far only just now. They learn. They learn! They not only learn, but they learn even in death! How deeply wretched can this place be?","color":"aqua"}
execute as @s[scores={rr.trigger.knowledge_id=3}] run tellraw @s {"text":"Almost one year has passed now since I first fought with the Necrosculker. As I learn about it, it learns about me. It hates. It detests the world. And knowing this, I am more determined to put an end to it. They grow in strength as well as I do. I have slain an even stronger foe, but once more I find myself fearing that there is something more to battle with.","color":"aqua"}
execute as @s[scores={rr.trigger.knowledge_id=4}] run tellraw @s {"text":"At last, I am led to believe their powers are becoming limited. After so long without the constant expeditions, the sculk has reached a plateau—it is still very strong, but with no creatures left to merge its infection with, there is little strength to gain. Felling this final beast has been a journey on its own. And now I can finally leave this place. I have heard and seen enough of this darkness, yet I have a feeling it will follow me even so.","color":"aqua"}
execute as @s[scores={rr.trigger.knowledge_id=5}] run tellraw @s {"text":"It was commonplace in my younger years to hear of expeditions led into the Deep Dark. It was sometimes even the first mission that new recruits were sent on--a simple cleaning duty, meshed in with a bit of light combat, to prevent this ravenous \"sculk\" infestation from getting out of hand. It was perfect for unlearned adventurers. A dark, spooky place, filled with alien-like creatures, to test the mettle of those that were freshly-trained. The Empire even commissioned several outposts to be constructed to better accommodate the frequency with which recruits were sent there. But, as you can see, this wasn't to last forever. The war's expenses grew too great, and to the Monarch, keeping the land was more important than ensuring the sanctity of it...","color":"aqua"}
execute as @s[scores={rr.trigger.knowledge_id=6}] run tellraw @s {"text":"... Soon, efforts to maintain the sculk infection became few and far between, and those sent out on those rare occasions began coming back with more horrific stories, to the point that some of them lost their sanity upon returning... increasingly, the question became “if” they would return, and no longer “when”. What those on the surface blatantly failed to account for was that sending anyone to die in the Deep Dark was akin to giving their undying loyalty to a greater enemy. One even worse than what was faced in the war...","color":"aqua"}
execute as @s[scores={rr.trigger.knowledge_id=7}] run tellraw @s {"text":"... First passed off as attempting to avoid the draft for the war, these nightmarish tales only evolved with each expedition. Recruits would seldom come back without mentioning a dreadful, inhuman whining and droning. Children got hold of their harrowing tales. They spread like wildfire, and I soon heard them too. I quite well remember one man describing the noise: \"it would reverberate throughout the entire cavern, as though the very walls themselves were alive, and they were furious.\" I was still but a teenager in these times, but the thought gripped me with cold fear. Indeed, my own imagination would be the first of its weapons used against me...","color":"aqua"}
execute as @s[scores={rr.trigger.knowledge_id=8}] run tellraw @s {"text":"... In death, it was strengthened. But in the droves of lives it managed to claim during that time, it grew beyond strength. It gained a wicked sentience. Or perhaps it always had one, waiting to be unleashed. And once the Empire fell, it became what it is today. Unstoppable. The Sculk infection ravaged the world, though it could never reach the surface. I tried many times to go see it myself after the Empire's fall, but to be truthful, my nerves with that place have never quite left me. One day I will be stronger and try once more. Though perhaps encountering something they describe as a sculk-infested necromantic monstrosity is not something I should pursue much more.","color":"aqua"}

scoreboard players set @s rr.trigger.knowledge_id 0
scoreboard players enable @s rr.trigger.knowledge_id